  Why String Pool is used?

-> String Pool is used to save memory.
                          
                          Example:
                          
                          String s = "java";
                          String t = "java";

                    Without String Pool, Java would create two "java" objects.
                    But with String Pool, Java creates only one "java" object and both variables point to it.



                                                                                          STACK MEMORY                         HEAP MEMORY
                                                                                          --------------------                 --------------------------
                                                                                          main() stack frame                    String Pool
                                                                                                                                --------------------------
                                                                                          s  -------- reference ------------\
                                                                                                                              \
