                                                      4: Stack and Heap Memory
=====================================================================================================================================================================

Java memory has many parts, but for now focus on only these two:

1. Stack Memory
2. Heap Memory


1. Stack Memory
================
Stack memory stores:
                local variables
                method calls
                reference variables
                primitive values

Example:
========
                public static void main(String[] args) {
                    int count = 10;
                    String name = "Rajat";
                }

Here:
        count = local primitive variable
        name  = reference variable

Both count and name are inside the main() method, so they are created in stack memory.


2. Heap Memory
===============

Heap memory stores:   
                  objects
                  String Pool
                  class-level object data

For String:      String name = "Rajat";   Actual "Rajat" object is stored in String Pool, and String Pool is inside Heap Memory.

Simple Diagram
================
                                                        String name = "Rajat";
                                                        int count = 10;
                                                        
                                                        Memory:
                                                        ++++++
                                                        
                                                        STACK MEMORY                         HEAP MEMORY
                                                        --------------------                 --------------------------
                                                        main() stack frame                    String Pool
                                                                                              --------------------------
                                                        name  -------- reference -------->    "Rajat"
                                                        
                                                        count = 10
                                                        --------------------                 --------------------------
                                                                                          
name does not store actual "Rajat" text.
name stores reference of "Rajat" object.
Actual "Rajat" is stored in heap memory/String Pool.


